Definition:
Final class cannot be subclass.
Used when no subclass is needed, ensuring its behavior remains unchanged.

Code:
final class FinalClass {
    void showMessage() {
        System.out.println("This is a method from a final class.");
    }
}

// Attempting to inherit the final class will cause a Compilation Error
// class SubClass extends FinalClass {
// }

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        FinalClass obj = new FinalClass();
        obj.showMessage(); // Directly using the final class
    }
}

Output:
This is a method from a final class.
